==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pail
<hw>Pail</hw> <pr>(p⟦amac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>paile</ets>, AS. <ets>p⟦ae⟧gel</ets> a wine vessel, a pail, akin to
D. & G. <ets>pegel</ets> a watermark, a gauge rod, a measure of wine,
Dan. <ets>p⟦ae⟧gel</ets> half a pint.]</ety> <def>A vessel of wood or
tin, etc., usually cylindrical and having a bail, -- used esp. for
carrying liquids, as water or milk, etc.; a bucket. It may, or may not,
have a cover.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pailful</ent>⟦br⟧
